        <!-- ============ SECTION 9: COMMON MISTAKES ============ -->
        <section class="section" id="mistakes">
            <div class="section-header">
                <p class="overline">Pitfalls</p>
                <h2 class="h1">7 Common NPS Mistakes</h2>
                <p class="body-lg">Research-backed pitfalls that skew your NPS data, and how to fix them.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="mistake-card"><div class="mistake-num">#1</div><h4>Surveying Too Frequently</h4><p class="body-sm">Response rates drop 40% after the 3rd survey in 90 days. Survey fatigue follows a linear decline: 68% &rarr; 58% &rarr; 46%. <span class="cite">CustomerGauge; UNM Research</span></p><div class="fix"><div class="fix-label">The Fix</div><p class="body-sm" style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Relationship NPS: maximum quarterly. Transactional: only after key events. Use Formbricks&rsquo; response cooldown to enforce automatically.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mistake-card"><div class="mistake-num">#2</div><h4>Not Segmenting Results</h4><p class="body-sm">You miss 2-3x variation between segments. A single NPS hides wildly different experiences across plans, tenure, and use cases. <span class="cite">Bain &amp; Company</span></p><div class="fix"><div class="fix-label">The Fix</div><p class="body-sm" style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Segment by plan tier, customer tenure, use case, and geography. Track each segment&rsquo;s NPS independently.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mistake-card"><div class="mistake-num">#3</div><h4>Ignoring Passives (7-8)</h4><p class="body-sm">Passives have 2x the lifetime value of detractors &mdash; making passive-to-promoter conversion the highest-ROI action. Yet most companies give them zero follow-up. <span class="cite">Bain &amp; Company</span></p><div class="fix"><div class="fix-label">The Fix</div><p class="body-sm" style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Ask passives: &ldquo;What would make you a 9 or 10?&rdquo; Use Formbricks conditional logic to route passives to a dedicated question path.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mistake-card"><div class="mistake-num">#4</div><h4>No Follow-Up Question</h4><p class="body-sm">Companies using conditional follow-ups collect 45% more actionable qualitative data. Without the &ldquo;why,&rdquo; NPS is just a number with no diagnostic power. <span class="cite">Formbricks data</span></p><div class="fix"><div class="fix-label">The Fix</div><p class="body-sm" style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Always include an open-text follow-up as question #2. Segment the follow-up by score range for richer data.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mistake-card"><div class="mistake-num">#5</div><h4>Wrong Timing</h4><p class="body-sm">Monday AM delivers 38% lower response rates vs Tuesday 10am. NPS placed as question #1 gets 12-18% higher completion vs. placed after 5+ questions. <span class="cite">Gainsight; MeasuringU</span></p><div class="fix"><div class="fix-label">The Fix</div><p class="body-sm" style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Send Tuesday-Wednesday, 9am-12pm in the recipient&rsquo;s timezone. Place NPS as the first question.</p></div></div>
            <div class="mistake-card"><div class="mistake-num">#6</div><h4>Not Closing the Loop</h4><p class="body-sm">Companies that contact detractors within 48 hours recover 70% of at-risk accounts vs 16% for those that don&rsquo;t follow up. Companies with any closed-loop process have +23 NPS on average. <span class="cite">Bain &amp; Company; CustomerGauge</span></p><div class="fix"><div class="fix-label">The Fix</div><p class="body-sm" style="color:var(--text-secondary);">Auto-alert your team via Slack/email on detractor responses. Set a 48-hour SLA for high-value accounts.</p></div></div>
